            "creation_date": 1321873821,
            "body": "<p>After some research amongst the various sites that hold java library sources it looks very much like <code>FileChannel.close<\/code> ultimately calls the <code>FileInputStream.close<\/code> or <code>FileOutputStream.close<\/code> of its parent object. <\/p>\n\n<p>This suggests to me that you should <strong>either close the FileChannel or the Stream but not both<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n<p>In view of this I am changing my original post to reflect one correct method, i.e. close the <code>Stream<\/code>s not the <code>Channel<\/code>s.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 8210815,
            "question_id": 8066130,
            "last_edit_date": 1343424010
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/409678a88624be6466e650f389ee8eaa?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 115659,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 303598,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/303598/matsev",
                "reputation": 34005,
                "display_name": "matsev",
                "accept_rate": 84
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 3,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1321124454,
            "creation_date": 1321122346,
            "body": "<p>If you are using Java 7, you could use <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/nio/file/Files.html#copy%28java.nio.file.Path,%20java.nio.file.Path,%20java.nio.file.CopyOption...%29\" rel=\"nofollow\">Files.copy(Path source, Path target, CopyOption... options)<\/a> for this operation to avoid writing, testing and debugging your own implementation.<\/p>\n\n<p>Alternatively, consider using an external library such as <a href=\"http://commons.apache.org/io/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Apache Commons IO<\/a>. Specifically, you will find <a href=\"http://commons.apache.org/io/api-release/org/apache/commons/io/FileUtils.html#copyFile%28java.io.File,%20java.io.File%29\" rel=\"nofollow\">FileUtils.copyFile(File srcFile, File destFile)<\/a> interesting:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>/** \n * Copies a file to a new location preserving the file date.\n * [...]\n * @param srcFile  an existing file to copy, must not be &lt;code&gt;null&lt;/code&gt;\n * @param destFile  the new file, must not be &lt;code&gt;null&lt;/code&gt;\n * [...]\n */\npublic static void copyFile(File srcFile, File destFile) throws IOException\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 8106559,
            "question_id": 8066130,
            "last_edit_date": 1321124454
        }
